==English==

===Etymology===
Portmanteau of '''''E'''ditor'' '''Mac'''ro'''s'''''.  

===Proper Noun===
'''Emacs'''

#{{computing}} A particular [[visual]] or [[WYSIWYG]] [[text editor]] (first written by Richard Stallman in 1975 but since reimplemented by others in several distinct versions), distinguished by its use of [[control character]]s as editing commands, by its lack of distinct "insert" and "edit" modes, and by its featurefulness and extensibility.